      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "An alternator acts as your vehicle's generator, converting mechanical energy from the engine into electrical energy to power your electronics and recharge the battery. You can likely tell it is failing if your dashboard warning light illuminates, headlights dim excessively when braking, or your battery dies immediately after sitting. Common signs also include strange buzzing or humming noises from the front of the engine and difficulty starting the car, so having a trusted mechanic perform a load test is the best next step.",
